commit.message: Added data_link_offset fix for PPPoE interfaces provided by pavm1654.
set 2.6.11 release date

[server] Fix ASAN-triggered crash in AFL fuzzing mode

This fixes a crash in initialization code when fwknopd is compiled
with ASAN support in AFL fuzzing mode via the
'afl/fuzzing-wrappers/server-enc-pkts.sh' wrapper script. This crash
is not in operational fwknop code - only special code that is
compiled in AFL mode.
[test suite] AFL: use afl-clang-fast by default, and fix memory limit which impacted ASAN AFL++ runs on 64-bit systems
[test suite] update test/spa_fuzzing.py to use Python3
[test suite] add 'asanfuzzing' argument to fko-wrapper Makefile
[lib] minor comment fix
ChangeLog and CREDITS updates
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:mrash/fwknop
Merge branch 'dstuart-dev-work'
Minor tweak to docs.
[test suite] paths fixes for Makefile.am tests
ChangeLog updates for 2.6.11
[test suite] prefer the 'ip' command to the older 'ifconfig' command

[test suite] Fix GPG SPA cycles that do not require 'no pw' key pairs

Add gpg.conf and gpg-agent.conf to set 'pinentry-mode loopback' to
restore GPG full cycle tests. This works with GPG 2.2.27 on Ubuntu. The
specific error that is fixed is shown at the end of the output below:
